function createBatch6Docs(folder) {

  // ── Doc 36: RavenStack Brand Guidelines ──
  createDocInFolder("RavenStack Brand Guidelines", [
    "# RavenStack Brand Guidelines",
    "",
    "Version: 2.0",
    "Effective: October 2025",
    "Author: Jen Nakamura, Marketing Lead",
    "Reviewed by: Alex Park (CEO), Li Wei (Design Lead)",
    "",
    "## Purpose",
    "",
    "These brand guidelines define how RavenStack presents itself to the world — in marketing materials, product interfaces, sales collateral, social media, events, and internal communications. Consistency is essential as we scale from 87 employees to 140 in 2026 and expand into new markets (UK, Germany, France). Every team member who creates customer-facing content should use this document as their reference.",
    "",
    "The guidelines were updated in October 2025 following our crossing of the 500-account milestone and the opening of the London office. The previous version (1.0) was written when we had 52 employees and served primarily US customers. Version 2.0 reflects our growth into a multi-geography, multi-vertical B2B platform.",
    "",
    "## Brand Identity",
    "",
    "### Mission",
    "RavenStack empowers teams to collaborate smarter with AI-powered tools that adapt to how they work.",
    "",
    "### Vision",
    "A world where every team has an AI-powered collaboration partner that anticipates their needs, surfaces the right information, and eliminates busywork.",
    "",
    "### Values",
    "- Transparent: We share our product roadmap, pricing, and even our challenges openly. Customers trust us because we are honest.",
    "- Collaborative: We do not just build collaboration tools — we practice collaboration internally. Cross-functional teamwork is in our DNA.",
    "- Relentlessly Useful: Every feature must solve a real problem. We do not build for demos or press releases. We build for daily use.",
    "- AI-First, Human-Centered: AI augments human decision-making, it does not replace it. Our AI features are tools, not autonomous agents.",
    "",
    "### Positioning Statement",
    "For mid-market B2B teams who struggle with tool sprawl and information silos, RavenStack is the AI-powered collaboration platform that combines project management, document collaboration, and intelligent automation in a single workspace. Unlike point solutions like Jira, Notion, or Slack, RavenStack provides 40 integrated features with 5 AI capabilities that learn from your workflow.",
    "",
    "## Brand Voice",
    "",
    "### Personality Traits",
    "- Confident but not arrogant: we know our product is good, but we do not talk down to competitors or customers",
    "- Technical but accessible: we can speak to engineering VPs and operations directors with equal clarity",
    "- Collaborative, not prescriptive: we show possibilities, we do not dictate how teams should work",
    "- Data-informed: we use numbers and evidence, not vague claims",
    "",
    "### Writing Examples",
    "- Good: 'RavenStack helps teams collaborate smarter with 40 features and 5 AI capabilities.'",
    "- Bad: 'RavenStack is the best and most powerful collaboration platform in the world.'",
    "- Good: 'Our Enterprise tier includes SSO, Audit Logs, and dedicated support for $199/seat/month.'",
    "- Bad: 'Get everything you need for an unbeatable price!'",
    "- Good: 'AI Search uses semantic embeddings to find documents based on meaning, not just keywords. In beta, it has achieved a 5.5% error rate with 492 uses.'",
    "- Bad: 'Our revolutionary AI technology will transform your workflow forever.'",
    "",
