  // ── Doc 37: Sales Enablement: Objection Handling ──
  createDocInFolder("Sales Enablement: Objection Handling", [
    "# Sales Objection Handling Guide",
    "",
    "Author: David Kim, Sales Lead",
    "Date: November 2025",
    "Audience: Sales team (AEs, SDRs), Partner sales teams",
    "Last Reviewed: December 2025",
    "Related: Competitor Analysis: AcmeSaaS, Competitor Analysis: NimbusApp, Pricing Strategy Review",
    "",
    "## Purpose",
    "",
    "This guide provides data-backed responses to the 10 most common objections our sales team encounters in competitive deals. Each objection includes the competitive context, the recommended response framework, supporting data points, and example language. The guide is updated quarterly based on win/loss analysis and product changes.",
    "",
    "In Q3-Q4 2025, David Kim's team tracked 45 competitive deals against AcmeSaaS. We won 28 (62% win rate) and lost 17. The objections documented here are the primary reasons cited in the 17 losses, supplemented by common objections from ongoing pipeline deals.",
    "",
    "## Objection 1: 'Too expensive compared to NimbusApp'",
    "",
    "Context: NimbusApp charges $99/seat/month with a single tier. Some DevTools and Cybersecurity prospects compare our Enterprise tier ($199/seat) unfavorably.",
    "",
    "Response framework:",
    "- Acknowledge the price difference directly — do not be defensive about pricing",
    "- Reframe the comparison from per-seat price to total cost of ownership",
    "- Highlight our land-and-expand pricing that NimbusApp cannot offer",
    "",
    "Recommended response: 'You are right that NimbusApp is $99/seat for engineering teams. However, RavenStack offers three tiers starting at $29/seat for Basic — that is 71% less than NimbusApp's single price. Our Basic tier is perfect for teams getting started. As you grow, Pro ($79/seat) adds advanced reporting and automation, and Enterprise ($199/seat) adds security certifications, SSO, and dedicated support. The total cost of ownership depends on your team's needs — many of our 168 Basic accounts started exactly where you are and scaled up only when they needed more.'",
