    "- Highlight what we DO have today",
    "- Offer interim measures for the deal cycle",
    "",
    "Recommended response: 'SOC 2 Type II is on our 2026 roadmap, targeted for Q2. I understand this may be a hard requirement for your procurement team. Here is what we have today: encryption at rest (AES-256) and in transit (TLS 1.3), SSO Integration (SAML 2.0 and OIDC), comprehensive Audit Logs for all admin actions, role-based access control, and quarterly penetration testing. Our Security Lead, Omar Hassan, is available for a technical security review call with your team. We also offer a detailed security questionnaire response and can provide our latest pen test results. Enterprise customers in FinTech (37 accounts) and Cybersecurity (31 accounts) are using these security features successfully today.'",
    "",
    "Data points:",
    "- SOC 2 Type II target: Q2 2026",
    "- HIPAA target: Q3 2026",
    "- ISO 27001 target: Q4 2026",
    "- Current Enterprise accounts in regulated verticals: FinTech (37) + Cybersecurity (31) + HealthTech (27) = 95 accounts using our security features",
    "- Win/loss: security certifications were cited in 12 of 17 competitive losses against AcmeSaaS",
    "",
    "## Objection 4: 'We are a small team, do not need Enterprise'",
    "",
    "Context: Smaller teams (5-15 people) sometimes hesitate at the Pro or Enterprise price point.",
    "",
    "Response: 'Absolutely — start with Basic at $29/seat. Many of our 168 Basic accounts are teams of 5-10 people. Our 100% trial-to-paid conversion rate shows the product delivers value fast. If you outgrow Basic, upgrading to Pro or Enterprise is seamless — your data, settings, and integrations carry over. Accounts that start on Basic and upgrade to Pro have a 95% retention rate — our strongest retention cohort.'",
    "",
    "## Objection 5: 'No mobile app'",
    "",
    "Context: AcmeSaaS has a mobile app rated 4.7 stars. We are web-only. Mobile was cited in 8 of 17 competitive losses.",
    "",
    "Response: 'Mobile app is a 2026 priority — development starts Q2 with a beta targeted for Q4. Today, our web app is fully responsive and works on mobile browsers. For push notifications, Smart Alerts (currently in beta with 378 uses) delivers to email and will support Slack and Teams soon. We believe a great mobile experience should be purpose-built, not a web wrapper — which is why we are investing in a native app rather than rushing a quick solution.'",
    "",
    "## Objection 6: 'We already use Jira/Notion/Slack — why switch?'",
    "",
    "Response: 'You do not have to switch — but consider the cost of three separate tools vs one platform. RavenStack replaces Jira (Sprint Planning, Kanban Board, OKR Tracker), Notion (Document Editor, Knowledge Base, Meeting Notes), and partially Slack (Real-time Chat, Notification Center) in a single platform with 40 features. The combined cost of Jira ($16/seat) + Notion ($15/seat) + Slack ($12.50/seat) = $43.50/seat — and that is without AI features or Enterprise security. Our Basic tier at $29/seat gives you all of this plus AI capabilities. Our Integrations Hub (3,457 uses, 3rd most-used feature) also connects to Jira, Slack, and other tools, so you can transition gradually.'",
    "",
    "## Objection 7: 'The onboarding seems complex'",
